sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor Customer
    participant UI as Mobile/Web App
    participant Orch as Onboarding Orchestrator
    participant Core as Account Service (Core Adapter)
    participant Legacy as Legacy Core Banking
    participant Kafka as Event Backbone
    participant Notif as Notification Service

    Note over Orch, Legacy: 1. Trigger Account Creation
    Orch->>Core: Command: Create Bank Account
    Core->>Legacy: Attempt message-based write
    
    Note right of Legacy: Core system is overwhelmed or times out
    Legacy-->>Core: Connection Timeout / Failure
    
    Note over Core: Circuit Breaker trips.<br/>Request saved to local queue for async processing.
    Core-->>Orch: 202 Accepted (ACCOUNT_CREATION_PENDING)

    Note over Customer, Orch: 2. UI Polling & Graceful Degradation
    loop UI Polling (Every 3-5s)
        UI->>Orch: GET /onboarding/{sessionId}/status
        Orch-->>UI: 200 OK (Status: ACCOUNT_CREATION_PENDING)
        Note over Customer, UI: UI shows: "We’re finalising your new account. You’ll get a message shortly"
    end

    Note over Core, Legacy: 3. Background Processing (Traffic Shaping)
    Core->>Legacy: Drip-feed queued request (Retry)
    Legacy-->>Core: Account Created Successfully

    Note over Core, Notif: 4. Event Publication & Choreography
    Core->>Kafka: Publish account.opened event
    
    par Asynchronous Notifications
        Kafka->>Notif: Consume account.opened
        Notif-->>Customer: Send Welcome Email/SMS
    and Orchestrator State Update
        Kafka->>Orch: Consume account.opened
        Note over Orch: Update session status to COMPLETED
    end